# Claude usage widgets — credentials for the 5h / combined widgets.
#
# These let the widget read your account's rate-limit usage from claude.ai.
# The CONTEXT-only widget (ctw) does NOT need this file — it reads local transcripts only.
#
# SETUP
#   1. Copy this file to:  %USERPROFILE%\.claude\claude_usage.env
#      (i.e. C:\Users\<you>\.claude\claude_usage.env)
#      Or keep it next to the .ps1 files, or point $CLAUDE_LIMIT_ENV at it.
#   2. Fill in the three values below.
#   3. Launch a widget (cuw.bat / ccw.bat). No file = the 5h line shows "no .env".
#
# HOW TO GET THE VALUES (from a browser logged in to claude.ai):
#   Open DevTools (F12) -> Application -> Cookies -> https://claude.ai
#   - SESSION_KEY : the value of the "sessionKey" cookie (starts with "sk-ant-sid01-...").
#   - DEVICE_ID   : the value of the "anthropic-device-id" cookie (optional but recommended).
#   ORG_ID:
#   - In DevTools -> Network, open any request to /api/organizations/<ID>/...; the <ID> (a
#     UUID) is your ORG_ID. Or visit claude.ai/settings and copy it from the URL/requests.
#
# SECURITY: SESSION_KEY is a live login token. Treat this file like a password —
# never commit your filled-in copy. Only this .example (with placeholders) belongs in git.

SESSION_KEY=sk-ant-sid01-REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-SESSION-KEY
ORG_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
DEVICE_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
